    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26b.40"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">40</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        705 Polk Blvd.
                        Des Moines 12, Iowa
                        August 29, 1958
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>University of Missouri</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I am sending you a copy of the piece I wrote for <hi rend="caps">ELEMENTARY ENGLISH</hi> (published by the National Council of Teachers of English at Urbana, Illinois). Please let me know what you think of the idea.</p>
                
                <p>Of course this is the first draft and it can be changed. I sent Mary Gunnett a carbon copy, and she is planning to use the idea with her high school English class this year. She teaches both Speech and English and thinks your <hi rend="caps">RED CLOUD</hi> would make a wonderful choral reading.</p>
                
                <p>I don't know whether publishers like to have a suggestion printed that classes should <hi rend="underline"><del>x</del><add>c</add>opy</hi> the text. I won't say much about that, but of course to have pupils use this as a choral reading one needs about a dozen copies.</p>
                
                <p>The address for your recording may be wrong. I wrote to this address about one week ago but haven't ha<del>ve</del><add>d </add>time for a reply.</p>
                
                <p>I have already<del>d</del>written my column <hi rend="caps">IDEA INVENTORY</hi> for October, November, and December. I may use this in January, if it meets with your approval. Mary Gunnett thought it a wonderful idea.</p>
                
                <p><hi rend="caps">ELEMENTARY ENGLISH</hi> is for grades 1 through 8, or I would write another type of article. Of course most of your <hi rend="caps">CYCLE OF THE WEST</hi> is too mature for such young children.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely yours,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Louise Hovde Mortensen</signed>
                
                    <signed>Louise Hovde Mortensen</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <note type="recipient">ansd</note>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
